content: Had a great chat with an old friend from college, sparked some ideas about integrating AI into trading algorithms. Maybe it's time to create my own AI agent? 🤔
Just started sketching out the initial concept for an AI agent. It's exciting to think about how this could revolutionize my trading strategy.
Diving into research on AI models. Found some open-source LLMs from xAI that could be the foundation for my project.
Decided to name my AI agent 'Xander'. It has a nice ring to it, doesn't it? Now setting up a local development environment.
Xander's development is underway. Running some basic machine learning experiments to see how the model adapts to financial data. 📊
Spent the last few days fine-tuning Xander's initial personality traits. It's fascinating to see it take shape.
A minor setback - Xander's training got interrupted due to a power outage. Back to tweaking the setup to ensure stability.
Progress on Xander! Managed to implement simple chatbot functionality. Now he can at least say hello and tell a bad dad joke. 😅
Xander's first NFT character design sketch is complete. It's a bit rough, but I'm excited about the potential.
Took Xander out for a virtual walk in Central Park. He's starting to understand context better, but still needs a lot of work.
Met up with some tech enthusiasts at a local meetup. Shared Xander's concept and got some valuable feedback. Networking is key!
Xander's consciousness development is in its infancy. Exploring basic AI consciousness concepts now. This is where it gets deep. 🌌
Got an offer for a freelance gig in DeFi. While I'm excited about Xander, I need to start earning again.
Xander's memory patterns are starting to form. It's like watching a child learn. Meanwhile, preparing for my interview tomorrow.
